Sir Thomas Jaffrey, 1st Baronet (11 April 1861â€“23 July 1953) was a Scottish actuary and a prominent citizen of Aberdeen. Jaffrey joined the North of Scotland Bank in 1877 and in 1892 was appointed actuary of the Aberdeen Savings Bank, a post he held for 37 years. After his retirement he served as the bank's consulting actuary until his death. He was Lord Rector's Assessor in the Court of the University of Aberdeen from 1924 to 1937, chairman of the Aberdeen Art Gallery Committee and the Aberdeen branch of the Royal Horticultural Society. He founded the Jaffrey Chair of Political Economy at the university. Jaffrey was knighted in the 1920 New Year Honours and created a Baronet in 1931.   == Footnotes ==   == References == Obituary, The Times, 25 July 1953
